cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with rate allocation for QoS-aware networking applications, which is a topic that falls under the scope of computer networks (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a novel time-coupling constraint, which involves considering the delay-sensitivity of sources, and incorporates it into the rate allocation algorithm. This constraint is related to control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the paper proposes a distributed algorithm for rate allocation, which involves communication between different nodes in the network, and thus falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC).
